  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pituitary adenomas can cause compression of optic nerves and chiasm, which will lead to
      damage of vision. This study aims to evaluate the predictive factors for recovery of vision
      in patients with pituitary adenomas following trans-sphenoidal surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
